Sentencas: Cu surface modified nickel foam is obtained by heating copper coated nickel foam in a reducing atmosphere.
Titulo: Surface modified Ni foam as current collector for syngas solid oxide fuel cells with perovskite anode catalyst

Sentencas: La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta (LSCM) perovskite oxide is prepared using a sol-gel combustion method.
Titulo: Surface modified Ni foam as current collector for syngas solid oxide fuel cells with perovskite anode catalyst

Sentencas: The modified foams and LSCM powders exhibit excellent resistance to carbon deposition in syngas at high temperatures.
Titulo: Surface modified Ni foam as current collector for syngas solid oxide fuel cells with perovskite anode catalyst

Sentencas: Furthermore, Cu modified foams show better mechanical strength compared to bare Ni foam, which readily cracks after exposure to syngas at high temperature.
Titulo: Surface modified Ni foam as current collector for syngas solid oxide fuel cells with perovskite anode catalyst

Sentencas: LSCM retains its perovskite structure during exposure to syngas or carbon monoxide at 900 C for 10 h. Cu surface modified Ni foam current collector demonstrates good chemical compatibility with LSCM in syngas atmosphere at high temperature.
Titulo: Surface modified Ni foam as current collector for syngas solid oxide fuel cells with perovskite anode catalyst

Sentencas: Syngas solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are assembled using Cu modified Ni foam anode current collector, LSCM anode catalyst, YSZ electrolyte, and porous Pt cathode.
Titulo: Surface modified Ni foam as current collector for syngas solid oxide fuel cells with perovskite anode catalyst

Sentencas: The present fuel cell provides similar power density to one with gold anode current collector and has excellent stability during operation at 900 degrees C. (C) 2010 Professor T. Nejat Veziroglu.
